<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, April 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME -- Italy's ruling center-left coalition on Friday morning
named current Treasury Minister Gulio Amato as candidate for prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
The nomination was announced by the ruling Left Democratic
Party's parliamentary leader Fabio Mussi, after his meeting with
Italian President Carlo Azeglio Ciampi Friday morning. (Italy-
Prime Minister-Candidate)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin arrived in Athens
Friday for a state visit to Greece at the invitation of Greek
President Costis Stephanopoulos.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit of a Chinese president to the country.
During the visit, Jiang is expected to exchange views with
Stephanopoulos and other Greek leaders on bilateral ties and major
international and regional issues of common concern. (Greece-Jiang-
Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Israel continued its attacks Friday morning in south
Lebanon and one Hezbollah guerrilla was killed in the air raids,
People's Sound radio station reported.
</P>
<P>
The radio reported that Israel warplanes launched four missiles
at the region near Nabatiye, bombing several villages. One bomb
fell on a market of Nabatiye but did not go off. (Lebanon-
Hezbollah-Israel)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI-- Six West African states outside the franc zone of the
African Financial Community Thursday night adopted a communique
with a strong commitment to creating a second monetary union in
the sub-region by January 2003, Ghana News Agency reported on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the communique, which was available Friday morning,
presidents or their representatives from Ghana, Gambia, Guinea,
Liberia, Nigeria and Sierra Leone said the union would be launched
after all the convergence criteria laid by the 22nd ECOWAS summit
last year are met. (ECOWAS-Communique)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Following meetings with the United Nations
Children's Fund (UNICEF), a verbal agreement on a temporary cease-
fire for the May 1-3 round of polio immunization has been issued
by the Taliban Militia and its opposition, the Northern Alliance ,
according to a press release from the office of the UN Coordinator
for Afghanistan here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"This is a positive step, now we hope that these commitments
will be met," said the Afghanistan UNICEF Representative, Louis-
Georges Arsenault. (Pakistan-Afghanistan-Cease-Fire)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- Belgium Friday played down Austrian Defense
Minister Herbert Scheibner's threat to ban flights over Austria by
Belgian military aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian Foreign Ministry said Scheibner's remarks were not
a decision of the Austrian government. (Belgiuim-Austria-Threat)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian State Duma, lower house of parliament,
Friday overwhelmingly ratified the Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban
Treaty (CTBT) by a vote of 298-74 with three abstentions.
</P>
<P>
The voting was held behind closed doors, and by law at least
226 votes in the 450-seat Duma were needed for the approval of the
treaty. (Russia-CTBT-Approval)  
</P>
</TEXT>
