<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Appoints War Hero to Fight Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 21 (Xinhua) -- One of Sri Lanka's most decorated
war heroes has been appointed commander of the army's northern
forces as battles were raging in northern Jaffna peninsula on
Friday between government troops and separatist rebels of
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE).
</P>
<P>
Deputy Chief of Staff Major General Janaka Perera would be
overall operations commander for both Jaffna and Wanni and he flew
to the northern Jaffna peninsula on Thursday to halt an ongoing
offensive by LTTE rebels, military officials said.
</P>
<P>
General Perera, also a senior officer of the anti-terrorist
commando regiment, was in charge of the forces that ousted the
Tamil Tigers from their stronghold of Jaffna in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The new appointment followed reports that the Sri Lankan army
is facing a serious debacle in the ongoing war in Jaffna.
</P>
<P>
A military spokesman said heavy fighting was still going on
around the Iyakachchi base on the Jaffna Peninsula Friday.
</P>
<P>
Troops have not lost their supply route, he said.
</P>
<P>
Perera is expected to re-plan strategies following reports of
heavy casualties among security forces during the past several
days.
</P>
<P>
At least 33 soldiers were killed and more than 250 injured
since the LTTE launched a fresh attack on April 18 to capture the
strategic Elephant Pass, a narrow causeway linking the peninsula
with the mainland.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, air force jets bombed rebel locations to prevent
the LTTE from capturing the strategic Iyakachchi military base,
the last bastion protecting Elephant Pass, as the rebels said they
had overrun several military camps.
</P>
<P>
Up to 20,000 troops are engaged in heavy fighting exchanges
with the rebels who have been fighting for a separate homeland for
minority Tamils in Sri Lanka's north and east since 1983.
</P>
<P>
A statement released from the LTTE's London office on Thursday
said that they were closing in on the strategic base of Iyakachchi
in Jaffna as a part of their efforts to recapture Jaffna from
government control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
