<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Index Loses Ground </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The key indicator on the Karachi
Stock Exchange (KSE) Friday shed 33.18 points, or 1.64 percent, to
1991.66 after heavy profit taking by the speculators.
</P>
<P>
The capital market which was bullish on Wednesday failed to
sustain the gains and hardly managed to stay up the 2000 mark on
Thursday despite profit taking mainly by the fiber sector.
</P>
<P>
Consequently, the market opened weak Friday and remained
bearish owing to profit taking on the weekend session.
</P>
<P>
A drastic cut in the volume was recorded, from 326.11 million
shares on Thursday to 182.07 million shares. The market capital
also slipped from 513.01 billion rupees (9.86 billion U.S. dollars)
to 505.60 billion rupees (9.72 billion dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
