<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Summit Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 21 (Xinhua) -- A mini Summit on Zimbabwean land
reforms concluded Friday evening in Victoria Falls, with
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe won support for the land
redistribution plan in the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here, Presidents from South
Africa, Namibia and Mozambique expressed their support for Mugabe
and urged international funding for land redistribution to end
Zimbabwe's crisis over the ownership of farms.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique President Joaquim Chissano told reporters that
western governments should make good on their promise at a 1998
donor conference to fund the redistribution of farm lands mainly
owned by whites. 
</P>
</TEXT>
