<HEADLINE> Iranian Defense Minister to Visit Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Defense Minister Rear
Admiral Ali Shamkhani will launch a ground-breaking visit to Riyadh
in the near future to expand military cooperation between the two
countries, the Islamic Republic News Agency said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Shamkhani will leave here with a high-ranking political and
military delegation for Saudi Arabia in the next few days, the
first one by a senior Iranian defense official since the 1979
Islamic revolution, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Defense Ministry spokesman Keyvan Khosravi said that
Shamkhani's visit will be in response to the visit of his Saudi
counterpart Prince Sultan ibn Abd al-Aziz to Tehran in April last
year.
</P>
<P>
Khosravi said that Shamkhani will discuss the potentials of the
two countries, the expansion of the bilateral ties and the issues
of mutual interests with Saudi officials during the visit.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian minister will also inspect major military centers in
Saudi Arabia, he added. 
</P>
<P>
During Prince Sultan's visit to Iran last year, the two
countries agreed to exchange military attaches. 
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-Saudi relations have steadily improved since Iranian
President Khatami came to power in 1997. The two countries went
through years of mutual suspicion following Iran's Islamic
Revolution in 1979. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
