<DOCNO> XIE20000422.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> (Urgent) Clinton Defends Snatch of Cuban Boy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 22 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
defended the forceful seizure of Elian Gonzalez Saturday, saying
that the right thing has been done for the six-year-old Cuban boy.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said he totally supports Attorney General Janet Reno's
decision to send federal agents in to take the boy from his
Florida relatives.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters at the White House that Reno had gone to
great lengths to convince the Florida relatives to voluntarily
give up the boy, and was left with no alternative other than to
use force.
</P>
<P>
The law has been upheld and the right thing has been done, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
