<HEADLINE> Chinese President Awarded Athens Gold Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin was
decorated here on Saturday with a Gold Medal of Merit by Athens
Mayor Dimitris Avramopoulos, who praised Jiang and the Chinese
government for their contributions to the great achievements China
has scored in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Thanking Avramopoulos for the award, Jiang said the Chinese and
Greek peoples understand and support each other in building their
countries and advancing world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he is glad that cooperation between the two
countries has made remarkable progress in the fields of politics,
economy, culture and science and technology.
</P>
<P>
He believes that the friendly cooperative ties between the two
peoples will surely be pushed further ahead in the new century.
</P>
<P>
Avramopoulos said at the award-giving ceremony that the ancient
civilizations in China and Greece have become sources of cultures
in the East and the West.
</P>
<P>
He said China is developing fast and has been continuously
making progress in various fields while it is playing an
increasingly important role in the international community.
</P>
<P>
As an individual country and a member of the European Union,
Greece intends to cooperate with China, and such cooperation will
be conducive to the development and stability in the world, the
mayor said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
