<HEADLINE> Bangkok to Set Up Website for Olympiad 2008 Campaigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Bangkok, bidding for hosting the
International Olympic Games 2008, is setting up a website to
launch its official campaigns and publicize the city readiness for
the huge sport event, an official report disclosed here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok Metropolitan Administration (BMA) has authorized
Master Ad Co., a local advertising company, to design the webpage
to describe the Thai capital city's preparations for the host of
the prestigious sport event in terms of stadiums, accommodations,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
It said in the initial stage, the official campaigns would
focus on gaining the public support in the country, as unity of
the people in a contending city is one of major factors which the
International Olympic Committee will take into account in choosing
a host.
</P>
<P>
The campaigns would then be expanded to garner support from
foreign countries, it noted.
</P>
<P>
The website, bangkokolympic2008.com, will also feature tourist
attractions, as well as cultures, and traditions in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Bangkok has been picked as one of the last five official
contenders in the race to host the 2008 Olympics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
