<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Juventus Win, Moving Closer for Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Alessandro Del Piero scored a
penalty for a 1-0 victory over Fiorentina, moving Juventus even
forward to the title of the Italian Serie A league on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Juventus, who have 68 points, maintained a five-point lead over
second-placed Lazio, who beat relegated Piacenza 2-0, with three
games to go in the season.
</P>
<P>
Argentines Diego Simeone and Juan Veron scored the two goals
for Lazio, but the victory seemed piled up little blocks to
Juventus title running.
</P>
<P>
Champions AC Milan moved back into third place on 54 points
with a 2-1 win at Reggina, edging out Parma on goals difference.
Parma extended their unbeaten record to eight games with a
goalless draw at AS Roma.
</P>
<P>
Inter Milan crushed Bari 3-0 for their first win in seven
matches, clawing to fifth on 52 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
