<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A Large number of dead seals
were discovered at a Kazakh islet in the Caspian Sea, Interfax
news agency quoted Kazakhstan's Emergency Situations Bureau as
saying on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Local fishermen reported Thursday that 50 seals were found dead
at the Shalyga islet, according to Interfax.
</P>
<P>
No explanation was given for the deaths, but Interfax said the
dead seals were newly borns.
</P>
