<HEADLINE> Egyptian Woman Painter Holds Painting Show in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Kawther Elsherif, an Egyptian
woman painter, held an exhibition of her paintings here today.
</P>
<P>
Thirty pictures entitled "From the Nile to the Yangtze River,"
provide a visual illustration of Elsherif's personal feelings
toward these two rivers and people and the people of Egypt and
China.
</P>
<P>
Critics said that these two ancient civilizations nurtured her
inspiration to create her masterpieces, including The Great Wall,
Pureness, Lotus Flower, and Seaside View.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Consul to Shanghai Adbel Fattah Ezeldin commented that
Elsherif, "a Chinese culture aficionado, uses her brush to reflect
the beliefs and history of the people, leaving beauty in this
world."
</P>
<P>
The 20-day painting show is co-sponsored by Egyptian Consulate-
General in Shanghai and the Shanghai International Art Festival
Center. 
</P>
