<P>
KAMPALA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
has returned from Victoria Falls in Zimbabwe where he attended a
one-day regional summit on the peace process in the Democratic
Republic of the Congo (DRC), said a press release from the Ugandan
President's Office on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The summit reviewed the progress so far made in implementing
the Lusaka Cease-fire Agreement, and also discussed other issues
concerning the conflict and the prospects for peace in the DRC,
the release said.
</P>
<P>
Joachim Chissano, president of Mozambique and chairman of the
Southern African Development Community, was quoted as saying that
the meeting in Victoria Falls was fruitful and offered good
results that can advance the solution to the problems in that
country.
</P>
<P>
The meeting had strengthened the political will to find
solutions in the DRC, and will help implement the Lusaka agreement
and the decisions of the recent Joint Military Commission
Agreement worked out in Ugandan capital city Kampala, he added.
</P>
