<HEADLINE> Tide-Watching Starts in East China's Haining </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The spring tide-watching was
started today in Haining, in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The tide of the Qiantang River near Haining is one of China's
natural wonders. Scientists say that the bell-shaped mouth of the
Qiantang River forms a tide 3.5 meters high.
</P>
<P>
Numerous other activities are scheduled including cultural and
artistic performances, forums and an exhibition on the late
Chinese poet Xu Zhimo, a native of Haining, tourist commodity
fairs as well as trade talks.
</P>
<P>
The tide-watching will last till early May.  
</P>
