<HEADLINE> China to Build More Power Transmission Works </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 22 (Xinhua) -- China National Power
Corporation will inject 30 billion yuan (3.61 billion U.S. dollars)
in the next five years to build works to connect seven trans-
regional power grids to facilitate transmission of electricity
from China's western to eastern regions.
</P>
<P>
Three major transmission routes from the west to the east are
now operational. Transmission routes have played a positive role
in improving power grids and stabilizing electricity prices, as
well as reducing pollution.
</P>
<P>
A corporate executive told Xinhua that preparations for linking
up local power grids from Shandong, Guangdong and central China
will be accelerated during the tenth Five-Year-Plan period (2001-
2005).  
</P>
