<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Sultan of Oman Qaboos Bin Said
arrived in the Qatari capital of Doha on Saturday on a three-day
visit, during which bilateral ties and a number of other issues
will be discussed.
</P>
<P>
A Qatari a statement on Friday said that Qaboos' visit comes in
response to an invitation from Qatar's Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin
Khalifa Al-Thani.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hamad and Sultan Qaboos will discuss means of boosting
bilateral relations, and international and regional issues, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Informed sources in Doha said Qatar "attaches great importance
to the meeting since it comes ahead of the second consultative
meeting of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) leaders" due in
Muscat, capital of Oman on April 29, according to reports reaching
here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are expected to discuss the most important
issues that will be on the agenda of the GCC consultative session,
said the sources without going into details.
</P>
<P>
The GCC, a regional political and economic alliance established
in 1981, comprises Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia and
the Untied Arab Emirates. 
