<HEADLINE> Name of Iranian Higher Education Ministry Changed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The name of Iran's Ministry of
Culture and Higher Education has officially been changed into the
Ministry of Science, Research and Technology, the Islamic Republic
News Agency reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The idea behind the measure was to pave the way for some
structural changes that are to be made in this ministry, said the
agency, adding that Mostafa Moin will remain the head of the new
ministry.
</P>
<P>
In a session here Saturday attended by officials of the
ministry, President Mohammad Khatami was briefed on the activities
and responsibilities of the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Cooperatives Minister Morteza Haji revealed
that President Khatami had started reviewing the performances of
his ministers in order to reshuffle his cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The government also has plans to merge the Agriculture Ministry
with the Construction Jihad Ministry and the Industries Ministry
with the Ministry of Mines and Metals.
</P>
<P>
But on April 13, Iran's moderate Minister of Culture and Islamic
Guidance Ataollah Mohajerani, who is also government spokesman,
denied reports that Khatami were planning to reshuffle the cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Mohajerani was impeached by the conservative parliament last
year for his support for press freedom. But he survived.
</P>
<P>
Iran has been clouded by political tension since the sensitive
sixth parliamentary elections in February, in which reformers
allied to President Khatami dealt a severe blow to the
conservatives by bagging more than 75 percent of the total 290
seats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
