<HEADLINE> Russian Rocket Explodes in Western Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A Russian mock-up rocket
exploded in western Kazakhstan Friday afternoon, the Interfax news
agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The rocket, which was launched from an air defense testing
range in Astrakhansky, Russia, and loaded with 16 kilograms of
explosives, blasted near a village in the Kurmangazinsky region of
the western Kazakh Atyrausky state, the report quoted the Kazakh
Emergency Situations Bureau as saying.
</P>
<P>
The blast left a crater of 2.5 meters deep and 4-5 meters wide
but did not cause any fatalities or material damage, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
Russia and Kazakhstan have set up a joint committee to
investigate the explosion. 
</P>
