<HEADLINE> Malaysia Appoints New Central Bank Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Saturday announced
the appointment of Zeti Akhtar Aziz as Bank Negara (State Bank)
Malaysia governor effective on May 1.
</P>
<P>
Zeti, 52, who is the first woman to be appointed to the top
post of the central bank, will succeed Ali Abul Hassan Sulaiman
who retires on April 30, the Finance Ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
She was acting governor after the resignation of former
governor Ahmad Don on September 1, 1998 and appointed deputy
governor six days later.
</P>
<P>
Zeti was appointed adviser to the central bank on July 1, 1995,
responsible for managing the bank's economics department, and was
later appointed one of the four assistant governors.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry did not say who would be taking over from
Zeti as deputy governor. 
</P>
