<DOCNO> XIE20000422.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pyongyang, Seoul Hold First Preparatory Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Delegations from the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and South Korea held their first
preparatory meeting at Panmunjom Saturday for an inter-Korean
summits scheduled to open on June 12-14, the Korean Central News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which was held in the Peace House just south of
the demilitarized zone bisecting the Korean Peninsula and runs
through Panmunjom, was attended by three representatives led by a
vice ministerial level official from each side.
</P>
<P>
Kim Ryong Song, head of the DPRK delegation, said that both
sides reaffirmed the three principles of national reunification
clarified in the July 4 joint statement.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the two sides agreed to continue at the next
contact the discussion on the working procedural matters related
to the inter-Korean Pyongyang meeting and summit talks, he added.
</P>
<P>
Kim pointed out that this is an important event of landmark
significance in improving the inter-Korean relations and settling
the reunification issue as it reflects the nation's will and
aspiration for independence
</P>
<P>
It is beyond doubt that a successful holding of the projected
meeting and talks would open an epochal phase in achieving
national reconciliation and unity and bringing earlier peace and
reunification, he said.
</P>
<P>
In a crucial breakthrough after a half-century of division,
Seoul and Pyongyang reached an agreement in Beijing on April 8,
under which South Korean President Kim Dae-jung will travel to
Pyongyang for a summit with DPRK leader Kim Jong-Il on June 12-14.
</P>
</TEXT>
