<HEADLINE> Applied Technology College Set Up in Qinghua University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- China's prestigious Qinghua
University today inaugurated a new college on applied technologies,
with Wu Minsheng as the head.
</P>
<P>
University sources said that software engineering will be the
major specialty in this newly-founded applied technology college.
</P>
<P>
Only science and technology university graduate students with
bachelor' diplomas and aged below 35 years will be eligible to be
enrolled for a two-year study at the new college.
</P>
<P>
Students on enrollment will finish all courses related to
computer software in the first year and go for practice in other
universities, and software or Internet-related companies in the
second year. Those who prove themselves qualified will get a
second bachelor's diploma.
</P>
<P>
The new college now only has 250 students who have all obtained
their first bachelor's diplomas. Forty percent of the students are
from big-name universities across the country.
</P>
<P>
Wu hopes that most of the graduates of his college will engage
in software designing and development, or go in for software
development and management in the fields of computer network and e-
commerce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
