<HEADLINE> China's Steel Production on Upswing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- China witnessed a steady growth
of steel production in the first two months this year, with the
output growing a year-on-year 4.8 percent to reach 19.81 million
tons, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of steel products hit 18.80 million tons in the two
months, surging 9.4 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Also in the period, production of pig iron grew by 11.0 percent
to reach 20.37 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The period also saw a year-on-year increase of 17.2 percent in
the output of non-ferrous metals, which stood at 1.11 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The output of aluminum oxide hit 688,300 tons, up 16.5 percent
on an annual basis, and that of aluminum products hit 184,400 tons,
surging 10.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output of copper products increased by 14.7 percent over
the same period of the previous year to reach 189,800 tons.
</P>
</TEXT>
