<HEADLINE> China's Output of Electrical Appliances Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The output of household refrigerators jumped 17.5 percent year-
on-year to 1.69 million, while that of color TV sets dropped 6.6
percent to 6.62 million.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures from the bureau show that the country
produced 2.03 million air conditioners in the January-February
period, soaring 23.3 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
In the same two months, the output of household washing
machines went up 6.6 percent to 2.64 million.
</P>
<P>
China has taken measures to stimulate domestic demand in a bid
to minimize the impact of the Asian financial crisis. Its anti-
smuggling drive has also promoted sales of China-made household
electric appliances.  
</P>
