<HEADLINE> China's Output of Chemicals on Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The production of chemical fertilizers climbed by 0.5 percent
on an annual basis to 4.76 million tons, and that of chemical
pesticides grew by 8.0 percent to 97,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
During the period, 948,400 tons of chemical fiber were produced,
up 10.8 percent year on year, while 1.34 million tons of plastic
products were turned out, up 15.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output of ethylene grew 6.3 percent on an annual basis to
716,000 tons and that of plastic resin and polymers jumped 25.9
percent to 1.63 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Production of caustic soda grew by 18.0 percent to 993,800 tons,
while that of sulfuric acid dropped 0.4 percent to 3.20 million
tons.  
