<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Rupiah Falls to Lowest in 6 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian rupiah exchange
rate against the U.S. dollar has plunged to the lowest level in
six months, touching 8,000 rupiah per U.S. dollar on Saturday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah traded at 7,875 per U.S. dollar (buying) and 8,000
rupiah per U.S. dollar (selling) in Saturday morning trade session.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed the falling of rupiah to the slow progress
of the government's program for economic restructuring within the
past two years.
</P>
<P>
"The significant weakening of the rupiah not only reflects the
country's political uncertainty but also the structural issues and
the failure of the International Monetary Funds (IMF) instrument,"
the Bisnis Indonesia daily quoted an economist at the country's
private Bank Mandiri, Martin Panggabean as saying.
</P>
<P>
Another dealer said that on Thursday there was a 'huge buying'
as much as 10 million U.S. dollars on Singapore market by a U.S.
investment bank which triggered panic among local speculators.
</P>
<P>
But the dealer added that the falling of rupiah has been also
triggered by a huge demand of dollar from local industries,which
have to pay their debt due within this year.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the Bank Indonesia (the central bank) said earlier
that private companies have to pay their foreign debt amounting to
29 billion U.S. dollars from January to December in 2000. This is
feared to influence the rupiah's exchange rate.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chairman of the National Economic Development
Council(DPUN) Sofyan Wanandi said the falling of the rupiah was
influenced by the country's current political condition.
</P>
<P>
"There are still many protests (against the government's policy)
. I think it has influenced the rupiah. We urge cabinet ministers
to pay more attention to their own task. We have to be serious in
handling the current economic situation and fasten the on-going
economic recovery," Wanandi said.
</P>
<P>
Early this week the rupiah was traded at 7,550 (buying) and 7,
675(selling) per U.S. dollar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
