<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Welcomes Russia's Aprroval of Nuclear Test Ban Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Ukrainian Foreign Ministry
welcomed the Russian State Duma's ratification of the
Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT) Friday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a statement that the Russian parliament's
approval of the Strategic Arms Reduction Talks (START) II and the
CTBT would produce a positive influence on the process of nuclear
nonproliferation and disarmament.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Ukraine, as one of the first countries
to sign the treaty, realized the importance of the CTBT and has
made substantial contributions to nuclear disarmament.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine also hopes the Duma's ratification could encourage
other countries with nuclear weapons to approve the treaty as soon
as possible.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Duma, the lower house of parliament, ratified the
treaty by a vote of 298 to 84 with two abstentions Friday.
</P>
<P>
The CTBT was passed at the 50th U.N. Assembly in September 1996
and has been signed by 155 countries. Only 53 countries have
ratified the treaty. Ukraine has submitted it to parliament for
approval. 
</P>
</TEXT>
