<HEADLINE> Preparatory Meeting for Inter-Korean Summit to Begin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANMUNJOM, South Korea, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Delegations from
Seoul and Pyongyang will hold their first preparatory meeting here
Saturday morning for an inter-Korean summit slated to open on June
12-14.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will kick off at 10 a.m. in the Peace House at the
truce village, just south of the demilitarized zone bisecting the
Korean Peninsula and runs through Panmunjom.
</P>
<P>
The three-member South Korean delegation to the meeting will be
led by Vice Unification Minister Yang Young-shik while the DPRK
counterpart will be headed by Kim Ryong-song, a senior counselor
of the Presidium of DPRK Supreme People's Assembly.
</P>
<P>
It will focus on the agenda and other procedural matters for
the historic inter-Korean summit.
</P>
<P>
The meeting comes 14 days after the two sides reached an
agreement in China, under which, South Korean President Kim Dae-
jung will travel to Pyongyang for a summit with DPRK leader Kim
Jong-il on June 12-14.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first inter-Korean meeting in the border village
since July 1994 when inter-Korean preparatory talks for a summit
between then South Korean President Kim Young-sam and the late
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) President Kim Il-sung
broke off due to the latter's sudden death. 
</P>
</TEXT>
