<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Road Pileup in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed and
six others injured Friday in a multiple collision in the Aramburu
speedway that unites Rosario with Buenos Aires, Argentina.
</P>
<P>
A police source said that the accident occurred Friday morning
when seven cars collided in dense fog that covered the area.
</P>
<P>
Two cars, which produced the first collision, were completely
destroyed, and to that impact were added a little afterwards two
vans and other three vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The drivers of two of the cars were detained, charged with
hitting and leaving the scene of the accident where two people who
died.
</P>
<P>
Another accident occurred Friday in Salta, in the north of the
country, killing three men and injuring three others in a head-on
collision of a car and a van in one route 80 kilometers south of
the Salta capital. 
</P>
