<HEADLINE> Top Legal News Items This Week in China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The following are top legal news
events in China this week:
</P>
<P>
Senior Lawmaker Expelled from CPC for Corruption, Adultery
</P>
<P>
Cheng Kejie, a vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), has been expelled from the
Communist Party of China (CPC) because of corruption charges, the
CPC Central Commission for Discipline Inspection said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The commission also proposed that Cheng be dismissed from his
post as a deputy to the NPC and his position as a vice-chairman of
the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Cheng's case will be transferred to judicial departments,
according to the announcement, as he was accused of taking more
than 4.5 million U.S. dollars in bribes and kickbacks in one of
the biggest cases of official corruption.
</P>
<P>
China Wins Decisive Battle Against Falun Gong: Official
</P>
<P>
An official with the State Council Press Office said Wednesday
that the Chinese government has won a decisive victory in its
ongoing battle against Falun Gong, but the cult group led by Li
Hongzhi has not recognized their defeat and continues to cause
trouble.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Legislature to Consider Six Laws in New Session
</P>
<P>
China's top legislature, the Standing Committee of the Ninth
NPC, is to hold its 15th session on April 25 to deliberate six
draft laws, NPC sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The new legislations will be: amendments to the law on
prevention and control of air pollution, an explanation of an
article of the criminal law, amendments to the law on product
quality, a draft law on farm seeds, and amendments to the customs
law. Each has been reviewed in previous legislative sessions.
</P>
<P>
Amendments to the law on the patent rights law will be
submitted to the legislators for a first hearing.
</P>
<P>
China Drafting Laws on Venture Capital
</P>
<P>
China is drafting laws and regulations on venture capital to
facilitate the growth of hi-tech companies, trade and legislative
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese legislature is also considering revising tax laws
and regulations regarding the administration for industry and
commerce according to international practices. China is planning
to develop a complete legal framework on venture capital.
</P>
<P>
Top Legislator Urges to Improve Democracy, Legal System
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, has urged to
develop China's market economy, improve democracy and the legal
system in the country during his recent tour to central China's
Hunan Province.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
