<HEADLINE> Top Legal News Items This Week in China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China to Adjust Agricultural Laws for WTO Entry
</P>
<P>
To strive for the development of China's agriculture when the
country joins the World Trade Organization (WTO), the top
legislature is taking radical measures to adjust its laws on
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
"The National People's Congress (NPC) and its Standing
Committee shall step up its legislation on agriculture, and revise
or abolish outdated laws as soon as possible," said Gao Dezhan,
chairman of the NPC sub-committee on agriculture, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Top Legislature to Inspect Enforcement of Laws on Rural
Enterprises, Land Management
</P>
<P>
China's NPC Standing Committee will send four inspection teams
to the countryside to see how effectively the Law on Rural
Enterprises is being enforced, and another three inspection teams
to inspect the enforcement of laws on land management.
</P>
<P>
500 kg of Drugs Seized by China's Customs in 1999
</P>
<P>
Chinese Customs Offices cracked over 150 drug cases,
confiscating more than 500 kg of drugs in 1999, an official from
the National Narcotic Control Commission said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said that there were 13 major cases involving some 400 kg of
drugs, or some 78 percent of the total. Besides, customs offices
across China seized more than 20 tons of chemical products used
for making drugs, 22 tons of poppyseed as well as more than nine
million psychedelic tablets. Customs officers also cracked 42 drug-
related mail cases, involving some 16 kg of drugs.
</P>
<P>
Armed Police Speed Up Modernization
</P>
<P>
China's People's Armed Police Force has speeded up the
upgrading of its command, monitoring, maintenance, and other
related systems with advanced telecommunications and Internet
technology.
</P>
<P>
Liberation Army Daily reported Tuesday that most of the armed
police corps in provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions
have created comprehensive combat command systems integrating the
use of computers and telecommunications technology.
</P>
</TEXT>
