<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Upset by Denmark in Opening Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 21 (Xinhua) -- European men's team champion France
was upset by Denmark 4-2 in the opening match at the European
Table Tennis Championship in Bremen on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Damien Eloi surprisingly lost to Denmark's Allan
Bensen 21-19, 21-19 in the opening rubber in the Group A round
robin match.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Philippe Gatien levelled it for France with a 21-12, 21-6
victory over Martin Monrad before Denmark's Michael Maze beat
Christophe Legout 21-19, 21-17.
</P>
<P>
The French levelled again at 2-2 after the doubles but then
Gatien and Eloi lost their rubbers to Allan Bentsen 21-14, 14-21,
18-21 and Maze 21-13, 17-21, 19-21 respectively.
</P>
<P>
France will next meet Austria on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sweden, the newly-crowned team world champions, had little
trouble beating Austria 4-0 while Russia beat Yugoslavia in the
other Group A tie.
</P>
<P>
In Group B, favorites Germany beat Belgium in four straight
matches as Poland beat England 4-1 and the Netherlands beat the
Czech Republic 4-2.
</P>
<P>
In the women's event, reigning European champions Germany had
little trouble getting past Group A rivals Sweden 4-1 in the first
round and then Italy 4-0 in the second.
</P>
<P>
Romania was first beaten by Italy 4-2 but then recovered to
beat France 4-0 in Group A.
</P>
<P>
Mihaela Steff lost her first two matches of the first round to
Laura Negrisoli 21-19 and 21-16 and Alessia Arisi 21-17, 21-19.
</P>
<P>
In Group B, European team silver medallists Hungary, were on
route to a semifinal berth by sweeping past Belarus 4-0 and then
by edging the Czech Republic 4-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
