<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100 GMT, Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT -- The Israeli forces bombed several villages in south
Lebanon Saturday morning and the shell hit a new school in the
village of Ibgeen, People's Voice radio station reported.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report on casualties after the raids.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian- and Syrian-backed Hezbollah guerrillas fired 10
Katyushas to two Israeli positions at Blaat and Tal Halfa in west
sector of south Lebanon. The Israeli radio confirmed the attacks
from guerrillas but did not release any damage result. (Lebanon-
Israel-Bombing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Palestinian sources asserted that a meeting will be held
on Sunday between chief Palestinian negotiator, Saeb Erekat and his
Israeli counterpart Oded Eran to discuss the last phase of the
Israeli pullout from the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
However, the sources quoted by the daily "Alayam" on Saturday
did not disclose the venue of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Israel has proposed to implement a part of
the troops redeployment before this month, including some
Palestinian villages near Jerusalem. (Palestine-Israel-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Five people, including a Spanish couple, were injured
Saturday when a fire demolished a downtown Cairo cinema and spread
to an adjoining residential block, security officials said.  The
ten-story block was immediately evacuated, as dozens of trucks from
the fire service, the police and the army tried to control the
fire, whose cause was not immediately known.
</P>
<P>
Five residents, including a Spanish couple, suffered slight
burns, and three apartments on the upper floors were severely
damaged, the officials said. (Egypt-Cinema Fire)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat arrived in Cairo
Saturday evening, in the wake of his talks with U.S. President Bill
Clinton in Washington, for talks with Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said earlier that he would
meet with Arafat later Saturday to discuss the outcome of Arafat's
talks Thursday with Clinton and U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Arafat will brief Mubarak on his visit in Washington
and the U.S. promise to directly involve itself in the upcoming
peace negotiations between the Palestinians and Israel, Moussa
said. (Egypt-Palestinians-Arafat Arrival)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian Defense Minister Rear Admiral Ali Shamkhani
will launch a ground-breaking visit to Riyadh in the near future to
expand military cooperation between the two countries, the Islamic
Republic News Agency said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Shamkhani will leave here with a high-ranking political and
military delegation for Saudi Arabia in the next few days, the
first one by a senior Iranian defense official since the 1979
Islamic revolution, the agency said. (Iran-Saudi Arabia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- Syria would not cede any of its rights or give up
any inch of its territory, said the central leadership of Syria's
National Progressive National Front.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the united front of the ruling Baath Arab Socialist
Party and other five major political parties met here Saturday
night. They listened to a report by Foreign Minister Faruk Shareh
on the latest developments of the peace process on the Syrian
track. (Syria-Israel) 
