<HEADLINE> 190 Die in Central America During Holy Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Some 190 people died in Central
America in the first days of Easter Week, said local press reports
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Eighty-nine of the victims were killed with a variety of
weapons and 55 died in road accidents, which left more than 1,000
injured.
</P>
<P>
The Central American countries with the highest number of
deaths are El Salvador with 53 casualties in violent conditions,
and Honduras with 46 deaths.
</P>
<P>
Panama and Costa Rica are the two countries with the least
deaths, with 13 and 14, respectively, said the press reports.
</P>
<P>
Some 36 people died in Nicaragua, five of them in an ambush of
former contras against a Nicaraguan Army patrol.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala reported 28 violent deaths, 13 of them with firearms,
12 in road accidents (five in a light plane crash), and three by
drowning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
