<HEADLINE> Colombia Confirms Soccer Player Kidnapped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's Atlantico Nacional
soccer team player Andres Estrada was kidnapped near the Carmen de
Bivoral municipality, northwest of Colombia, police confirmed
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The sportsman was traveling in a car with a woman and a minor
when he was intercepted Friday night by a group of four men and
two women, said Colombian police operative commander general
Alfonso Arellano.
</P>
<P>
The officer attributed the kidnapping of Estrada to the
National Liberation Army (ELN), the second biggest rebel group in
the country after the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC)
.
</P>
<P>
The soccer player's wife Alejandra Arias said that she has not
received any message from the kidnappers and that Estrada had
never been threatened.
</P>
<P>
The person who accompanied the football player said that one of
the kidnappers told Estrada that he had to meet with the "
commander of the group."
</P>
<P>
The wife of the soccer player asked the kidnappers to respect
the life of her husband and demanded them to release him
immediately.
</P>
<P>
The board of the Nacional club, the only Colombian team which
ever won the Libertadores of America Cup (1989), showed concern
for the fate of the player and said they hoped for the prompt
return of the player. 
</P>
</TEXT>
