<HEADLINE> Brazilian Demonstrators Fight Police, 141 Detained </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A total of 141 persons were
detained Saturday during a confrontation between 1,000
demonstrators and 200 military policemen near the Porto Seguro
municipality in the Brazilian state of Bahia.
</P>
<P>
A group of demonstrators of "Brazil, Another 500," formed by
Indians, the Landless Workers Movement (MST), the Workers Unique
Central, and other social groups, tried to jump a police control
point in Santa Cruz de Cabralia near Porto Seguro.
</P>
<P>
The celebrations for the 500 anniversary of the discovery of
Brazil will be held in this place Saturday afternoon and presided
over by Brazilian President Fernando Henrique Cardoso and his
Portuguese counterpart, Jorge Sampaio.
</P>
<P>
Policemen used tear gas and rubber bullets to scatter the crowd
that was demonstrating its disagreement with the celebration of
this date, and 141 demonstrators were detained.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian police have implemented a series of controls in
the main roads leading to Puerto Escondido to guarantee the
security in the commemorations.
</P>
<P>
President Cardoso canceled his visit to the indigenous village
of Corona Vermelha in view of the security problems and to prevent
bigger incidents.
</P>
<P>
According to historians, when Portuguese navigator Pedro
Alvares Cabral arrived in Brazil at the head of a Portuguese
expedition on April 22 of 1500, the territory had 5 million
indigenous people, most of whom were assassinated by the
Portuguese colonizers.
</P>
<P>
The last official statistics put the indigenous population at
350,000 people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
