<HEADLINE> 7 Killed in 2 Small Plane Crashes in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The reports said two people were killed when a small airplane
crashed in Shenandoah County in northwest Virginia.
</P>
<P>
The four-seat plane clipped some power lines and came within 15
meters of striking a house. The victims were the plane's occupants,
a man and a woman.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, five members of a family were found dead in the
wreckage of a small plane in the hills of southwestern Virginia
Saturday, more than a day after the plane disappeared from radar.
</P>
<P>
The single-engine aircraft was en route from Nashville,
Tennessee State, to Roanoke when it vanished from radar late
Friday morning near Norton.
</P>
<P>
Rescue teams, delayed by heavy clouds and rain, found the
wreckage Saturday afternoon not far from where the plane was last
seen on radar.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the two crashes was not immediately known. The U.S.
National Transportation Safety Board will investigate. 
</P>
